(217, 1, '2018-08-15 08:55:47', '2018-08-15 08:55:47', '\"How to Code in HTML5 and CSS3\" is aÂ <a href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0/\">free</a>Â e-book about making websites in HTML5 and CSS for absolute beginners. It doesn\'t require any experience in IT to start. The aim of this book is to show the art of making websites using a plain language which is full of practical analogies. After reading over 100 pages you will get to know the basic concepts and techniques of web development and be able to build your first website ever!\r\n\r\nhttp://howtocodeinhtml.com/', 'How to Code  in HTML5 and CSS3', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-to-code-in-html5-and-css3', '', '', '2018-08-15 08:55:47', '2018-08-15 08:55:47', '', 0, 'http://localhost/philosophy/?post_type=book&#038;p=217', 0, 'book', '', 0),
(218, 1, '2018-08-15 08:54:58', '2018-08-15 08:54:58', '', 'cover', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'cover', '', '', '2018-08-15 08:54:58', '2018-08-15 08:54:58', '', 217, 'http://localhost/philosophy/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/cover.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(219, 1, '2018-08-15 08:58:58', '2018-08-15 08:58:58', 'We understand that all kinds of people build websites these days (and that they donât all have a degree in computer science).\r\n\r\nSo, if you want to use JavaScript to make your web pages more interactive, interesting, and usable, we can help. Even if you have never done any programming\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttp://www.javascriptbook.com/', 'JavaScript and JQuery: Interactive Front-End Web Development', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'javascript-and-jquery-interactive-front-end-web-development', '', '', '2018-08-15 08:58:58', '2018-08-15 08:58:58', '', 0, 'http://localhost/philosophy/?post_type=book&#038;p=219', 0, 'book', '', 0),
(220, 1, '2018-08-15 08:58:47', '2018-08-15 08:58:47', '', 'javascript-and-jquery-book-cover', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'javascript-and-jquery-book-cover', '', '', '2018-08-15 08:58:47', '2018-08-15 08:58:47', '', 219, 'http://localhost/philosophy/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/javascript-and-jquery-book-cover.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(221, 1, '2018-08-15 09:00:42', '2018-08-15 09:00:42', 'If youâre a PHP developer, you can build Rails-like applications without learning a new language by following the hands-on tutorials inÂ <i>Professional CodeIgniter</i>. In this book, find an overview of MVC and agile technologies, model and schema for products, helpers and libraries, Ajax and Scriptaculous, and explanations of the creation of applications like content management, blogs, and forums. Follow the step-by-step instructions for building and perfecting each application with CodeIgniter, and you will learn how to avoid everyday problems that other reference manuals donât address.', 'Professional CodeIgniter', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'professional-codeigniter', '', '', '2018-08-15 09:00:42', '2018-08-15 09:00:42', '', 0, 'http://localhost/philosophy/?post_type=book&#038;p=221', 0, 'book', '', 0),
(222, 1, '2018-08-15 09:00:33', '2018-08-15 09:00:33', '', 'images (2)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'images-2', '', '', '2018-08-15 09:00:33', '2018-08-15 09:00:33', '', 221, 'http://localhost/philosophy/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/images-2.jpeg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(223, 1, '2018-08-15 09:03:00', '2018-08-15 09:03:00', 'From advanced selectors to generated content to the triumphant return of web fonts, and from gradients, shadows, and rounded corners to full-blown animations, CSS3 is a universe of creative possibilities. No one can better guide you through these galaxies than world-renowned designer, author, and CSS superstar Dan Cederholm. Learn what works, how it works, and how to work around browsers where it doesn\'t work.', 'Css3 for Web Designers', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'css3-for-web-designers', '', '', '2018-08-15 09:17:30', '2018-08-15 09:17:30', '', 0, 'http://localhost/philosophy/?post_type=book&#038;p=223', 0, 'book', '', 0),
(224, 1, '2018-08-15 09:02:44', '2018-08-15 09:02:44', '', '21+7kkWvWuL._BO1,204,203,200_', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '217kkwvwul-_bo1204203200_', '', '', '2018-08-15 09:02:44', '2018-08-15 09:02:44', '', 223, 'http://localhost/philosophy/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/217kkWvWuL._BO1204203200_.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(225, 1, '2018-08-15 09:35:31', '2018-08-15 09:35:31', 'Since<i>Â Donât Make Me ThinkÂ </i>was first published in 2000, hundreds of thousands of Web designers and developers have relied on usability guru Steve Krugâs guide to help them understand the principles of intuitive navigation and information design. Witty, commonsensical, and eminently practical, itâs one of the best-loved and most recommended books on the subject.', 'Don\'t Make Me Think, Revisited: A Common Sense Approach to Web Usability', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dont-make-me-think-revisited-a-common-sense-approach-to-web-usability', '', '', '2018-08-15 09:35:31', '2018-08-15 09:35:31', '', 0, 'http://localhost/philosophy/?post_type=book&#038;p=225', 0, 'book', '', 0),
